		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=223272"><span id="Sage">fhrugby</span></a><b><span id="Sage"><br>Sage</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="50" width="75" src="/uf/fhrugby/pirateflag.gif"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />544 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.72]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=fhrugby&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />In doing some research, I see that at level 20, rogues get the make poison skill.&nbsp;&nbsp;Is this a trade skill that you merely need to start doing (once you have the components)...or is this something that you have to train with a guild master first (i.e. invest a point)? I went to the PoK guildmaster after I hit 20, but didn't have skill listed...didn't have time to look around yet. Maybe in my home town? <hr size="1" /></blockquote>  <br /> <br /> <br />Make Poison does not require training first, you can start doing combines once you reach that level, and have bought a mortar and pestle from a rogue trader, there is thre in second floor of PoK Tradeskill building. <br /> <br /><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />Also, I keep seeing references to a rogue's ability to 'evade'...I take it this is some way to lose aggro after a big backstab....but I can't find this skill either. Can someone help me here? <hr size="1" /></blockquote>  <br /> <br />Evade is using the hide button while you have aggro on you, it lowers you on the hate list. To make it work, you need to hit the autoattack hotkey to turn attack off, then hit hide hotkey or button, then hit autoattack to turn back on attack. This works best with hide as a hot key, you can also be put in a macro. I have both, I use the macro when its a very busy fight, and hotkeys manually when it is not. (I prefer hotkeys manually when I can because macro has built in delay that is slightly longer than I can hit the hot keys.) <br />You will then see a message regarding if it was a successful evade or not. For best results use all battle long, do not wait until you have aggro already. <br /> <br />Every rogue should have this site on his fav list, they have tons of useful rogue info <a href="HTTP://eq.thesafehouse.org/" title="HTTP://eq.thesafehouse.org/" target="akztarg">the safehouse</a> <br /></p>
