		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=37685"><span id="Sage">Taushar the Wise</span></a><b><span id="Sage"><br>Sage</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />249 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.77]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Taushar&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>I can answer your second question first. The &quot;evade&quot; is a combination of skills you put together to evade the mob when you get aggro. It works when you are working with a tank to lose aggro back to the tank, not just to escape a mob all together. What you do is a sneak/hide combo. First you hit sneak then hide, that I believe lowers your aggro by 500 so the mob goes back to the bank. What I do is to make a hot key that does: <br /> <br />1. Stop attack <br />2. Sneak <br />3. Hide <br />4. Wait 1 sec <br />5. Backstab <br />6. re-engage <br /> <br />This gives me to stop attack, evade, then start the attack off with a back stab then re-engage.  <br /> <br />As for your first question, things have changed lately so I am not sure what the answer is today. I believe it is that you can start the poison making from level 1 now days. Used to be that when you hit 20, you can train at your trainer 1 point then you had the ability. I think now with current change, you have to learn from combines but you can do it at level 1. Not 100% sure though. <br /> <br />Taushar</p>
