		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.72]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=fhrugby&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />1. Stop attack  <br />2. Sneak  <br />3. Hide  <br />4. Wait 1 sec  <br />5. Backstab  <br />6. re-engage  <br /> <br />This gives me to stop attack, evade, then start the attack off with a back stab then re-engage. <hr size="1" /></blockquote>  <br />I respectfully disagree =) <br /> <br />You do not need line 2 - I never sneak to evade, and evade works fine and people have tested it and have posted at thesafehouse.org that there is no extra aggro reduction from adding sneak. Also is it not 5 line limit in a social? I do not have EQ here at work, but I would swear its 5.  <br /> <br />If you want to combine backstab and evade together I would not setup my macro as above for your level because you will lose too much attack time and therefore dps and DPS is a rogue main purpose in a group. <br /> <br />You would lose attack time from the delay line which is not needed and also even without the delay line, it will take time to backstab before autoattack is macroed and that would be uncessary lost dps time. Instead I would backstab before stopping attack. <br /> <br />1. Backstab <br />2. attack off <br />3. hide <br />4. attack on <br />5. <span class="sm">(cycle sense traps, and other useful abilities in this spot to train them up, note that if you put in disarm, begging or pickpocket they will cause increased aggro, and pickpocket/begging would need to be done before attack on)</span> <br /> <br />The only problem with doing backstab and evade in a combined macro is that backstab and hide/evade are on seperate timers and they are of differnt length and will not alway be ready at same time, therefore at your level you should follow the backstab timer for max possible dps and you will probably do 50% to 75% of the possible evades you could in a battle, but that should be enough. <br /> <br /><i>PS - RE: the delay line in evade macro. When you get to a the high end level, if you find you start to get too much aggro even with evade hit all the time, you may want to add in a delay as in the first macro just to reduce aggro from less dps. However reducing dps is the opposite of what rogue wants to do, that should be last option. I prefer to do evade manual at higher level as I can add the delay manually <b>if</b> I find I get too much aggro that particular mob. But starting out up to 60 a macro would do perfectly.</i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Thu Mar 31 15:40:25 2005 by fhrugby</span></i></p>
